    <p>de•con•struc•ted – an a cap­pella sound­scape</p>
    <p>The Es­planade’s mall walk­way has three con­i­cal sky­lights (right) with beau­ti­fully res­o­nant acous­tics which I have al­ways thought would be per­fect for choral per­for­mances. The arts cen­tre is now mak­ing use of the cones in this fun sound­scape in­stal­la­tion. This is part of its an­nual</p>
    <p>Voices – A Fes­ti­val Of Song, which is on till Sun­day.</p>
    <p>Five songs in Malay, Chi­nese, Tamil and Hokkien, recorded by a cap­pella group 1023, play on a loop. Each cone hosts a dif­fer­ent track of the song be­ing played, a great demon­stra­tion of the art of a capella.</p>
    <p>WHERE Es­planade – The­atres On The Bay (mall walk­way) MRT Es­planade</p>
    <p>WHEN Till Sun­day, 11am to 10pm daily</p>
    <p>AD­MIS­SION Free</p>
    <p>INFO str.sg/JEGp</p>

